  "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin>\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<style>\n*, *::before, *::after {\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n}\n\nbody {\n  width: 1280px;\n  height: 720px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  background: #050403;\n  position: relative;\n}\n\n.bg-glow {\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: 0;\n  background: radial-gradient(\n    ellipse 70% 80% at 66% 47%,\n    #1e0d03 0%,\n    #0c0602 40%,\n    #050403 68%\n  );\n}\n\n.bust-container {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  right: 0;\n  width: 860px;\n  height: 720px;\n}\n\n.bust-container img {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n  object-fit: cover;\n  object-position: center top;\n  display: block;\n  filter: sepia(0.22) contrast(1.12) brightness(0.70) saturate(0.82);\n}\n\n.bust-fade-left {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  left: 0;\n  bottom: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  background: linear-gradient(\n    to right,\n    #050403 0%,\n    rgba(5,4,3,0.90) 13%,\n    rgba(5,4,3,0.58) 28%,\n    rgba(5,4,3,0.14) 50%,\n    transparent 68%\n  );\n}\n\n.bust-fade-bottom {\n  position: absolute;\n  bottom: 0;\n  left: 0;\n  right: 0;\n  height: 160px;\n  background: linear-gradient(to top, #050403 0%, transparent 100%);\n}\n\n.bust-fade-top {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  left: 0;\n  right: 0;\n  height: 60px;\n  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #050403 0%, transparent 100%);\n}\n\n.candle-bloom {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  right: 0;\n  width: 860px;\n  height: 720px;\n  background: radial-gradient(\n    ellipse 48% 52% at 42% 34%,\n    rgba(255,168,55,0.07) 0%,\n    transparent 58%\n  );\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n\n.vignette {\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: 0;\n  background: radial-gradient(\n    ellipse at 63% 44%,\n    transparent 18%,\n    rgba(0,0,0,0.54) 100%\n  );\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n\n.text-block {\n  position: absolute;\n  left: 68px;\n  top: 50%;\n  transform: translateY(-52%);\n  white-space: nowrap;\n}\n\n.text-his {\n  display: block;\n  font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;\n  font-weight: 400;\n  font-size: 80px;\n  letter-spacing: 0.46em;\n  color: #C4A028;\n  line-height: 1;\n  text-shadow:\n    0 2px 14px rgba(0,0,0,0.97),\n    0 0 36px rgba(0,0,0,0.65);\n}\n\n.divider {\n  display: block;\n  height: 1px;\n  width: 596px;\n  background: linear-gradient(\n    to right,\n    rgba(196,160,40,0.62),\n    rgba(196,160,40,0.07)\n  );\n  margin: 20px 0 21px 1px;\n}\n\n.text-secret {\n  display: block;\n  font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  font-size: 158px;\n  letter-spacing: 0.04em;\n  color: #C4A028;\n  line-height: 0.84;\n  text-shadow:\n    0 0 65px rgba(196,160,40,0.08),\n    0 4px 22px rgba(0,0,0,0.98),\n    0 0 90px rgba(0,0,0,0.55);\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<div class=\"bg-glow\"></div>\n\n<div class=\"bust-container\">\n  <img src=\"{{IMG:1}}\" alt=\"Marcus Aurelius marble bust\">\n  <div class=\"bust-fade-left\"></div>\n  <div class=\"bust-fade-bottom\"></div>\n  <div class=\"bust-fade-top\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"candle-bloom\"></div>\n<div class=\"vignette\"></div>\n\n<div class=\"text-block\">\n  <span class=\"text-his\">HIS</span>\n  <span class=\"divider\"></span>\n  <span class=\"text-secret\">SECRET</span>\n</div>\n\n</body>\n</html>",
  "why": "The bust faces left so Marcus Aurelius appears to be looking directly at the words 'HIS SECRET' — he sees the viewer reading his private journal, creating an intimate complicity that no other framing achieves. 'HIS' is set small with wide spacing (a whispered setup) while 'SECRET' explodes at 158px (the revelation), and the thin gold divider between them functions like a held breath — it tells the eye to pause before the payoff. Warm amber Cinzel was chosen because it literally echoes the candlelight in the image: the text looks like it was lit by the same flame that lit his face, not designed in 2026. At 168×94px, near-black plus metallic gold is the highest-contrast warm-tone pairing in visual design — the stacked text block remains a legible golden stripe even when the face detail is invisible.",
